.TH FB2LESS 1 "14 May 2027" "0.9.8" "fb2less manual"
.SH NAME
fb2less \- Terminal-based FB2 reader
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B fb2less
[\fIFILE\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B fb2less
is a terminal ebook reader for FB2, EPUB, and TXT formats, written in Python using the curses library.
It supports reading directly from ZIP archives, footnote viewing, auto-scrolling, chapter and percentage navigation, and an advanced bookmarks manager. The enhanced EPUB parser ensures correct rendering of complex layouts and paragraph breaks. Users can customize colors (background, text, and headers), text width, and border styles. Settings are saved individually for each book. If FILE is not specified, the program automatically opens the last read book from history.
.SH OPTIONS
.IP "\-h, \-\-help"
Show a brief help message and exit.
.IP "\-v, \-\-version"
Show the program version and exit.
.SH KEYBOARD COMMANDS
.TP 20
.IP "o"
Settings: change interface language, scan path, and library cleanup.
.IP "K"
Switch interface language.
.IP "j, Down / k, Up"
Move text one line down or up.
.IP "d / u"
Scroll half a page forward or backward.
.IP "PgUp, Left"
Scroll one page back.
.IP "Space, PgDn, Right"
Scroll one page forward.
.IP "[, ]"
Jump to the beginning of the previous or next chapter.
.IP "P"
Jump to a specific percentage of the book.
.IP "i"
Display book information, technical metadata, and annotation.
.IP "Z"
Scan the current directory. Recursively searches for books, extracts metadata (author, series), updates the library, and removes entries for non-existent files.
.IP "L"
Open the library. Contains a list of books with search support (via / key) and sorting options.
.IP "s"
Change sorting mode within the library: by Title, Author, or Series.
.IP "Del / D"
Remove the selected entry from the library (does not delete the file from disk).
.IP "Enter"
Open the selected book in the library or Table of Contents.
.IP "t"
Open interactive Table of Contents.
.IP "f"
Sequential viewing of footnotes on the current page in a popup window.
.IP "/"
Search for text within the book.
.IP "n / N"
Find the next or previous search match.
.IP "m"
Set a bookmark at the current position. Bookmark text is automatically generated from the paragraph start.
.IP "M"
Open the bookmarks manager for navigation or deletion.
.IP "a"
Toggle auto-scroll on/off.
.IP "V"
.IP "V"
Toggle Text-to-Speech (TTS) mode. The application will read the text line-by-line, highlighting the current sentence and automatically turning pages. Pressing \fBV\fP again or exiting with \fBq\fP stops the speech immediately. TTS parameters, such as language and speech rate, can be configured in the settings menu (\fBo\fP).
.IP "s / S"
Increase or decrease auto-scroll speed (1-10).
.IP "c / b / v"
Change Text (c), Background (b), or Header (v) colors.
.IP "B"
Cycle through border styles: Window-frame, Text-focused, or No borders.
.IP "e"
Flip mode: instant page change or one of 4 sliding animation modes.
.IP "H"
Toggle Status Bar.
.IP "\-, ="
Decrease or increase the text block width.
.IP "h"
Show the built-in help window with commands grouped by category.
.IP "q"
Exit the program, saving reading position and current settings.
.SH FILES
.IP "~/.config/fb2less/"
User configuration and data directory.
.IP "~/.config/fb2less/history.json"
JSON file containing reading history, positions, bookmarks, authors, and book series information.
.IP "~/.config/fb2less/config.json"
JSON file with global settings (colors, width, language, scan path).
.SH AUTHOR
Written by measles.
